<br>
If a caster is using root to root adds/CC in a confined space, they should have a hotkey made for it and melees should know to back away from it. It's not a problem if a mob is rooted away from the main fighting. Casters also root a mob so that aggro transfers to the main tank and away from the enchanter, for example. If you're a melee class and not the main tank, try backing off for a second or two until the MT has and is holding aggro.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uabru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/02 7:53:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23952.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: root bug</span><hr size=1> It's also an indication that your barb rogue friend needs to back off in general, even on non-rooted mobs.  When spell-rooted, a mob has strict proximity agro, so if you are nearest, you WILL be the one the mob is beating on (not true for any casting the mob does).  However, all mobs have some degree of proximity calculated into their agro, and some mobs in Velious in particular, give a whole lot of weight to proximity when not rooted.  Any experienced rogue worth their salt will know to stand as far as possible from a mob while still being able to hit it, as that provides for the least amount of agro.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=126501">Abru</a>, Elder Hierophant on The Nameless,  <a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/index.shtml" target=_top>Legacy of Steel</a>, <a href="mailto:AbruEQ@hotmail.com">AbruEQ@hotmail.com</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usolwenarrowson